import { HttpErrorResponse } from '@angular/common/http'; import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core'; import { Employee } from './employee'; import { EmployeeService } from './employee.service'; @Component({ selector: 'app-root', templateUrl: './app.component.html', styleUrls: ['./app.component.css'] }) export class AppComponent implements OnInit { public employees: Employee[] | undefined; constructor(private employeeService: EmployeeService) { } ngOnInit() { this.getEmployees(); } public getEmployees(): void { this.employeeService.getEmployees().subscribe( (response: Employee[]) => { this.employees = response; }, (error: HttpErrorResponse) => { alert(error.message); } ); } }
